Finally! I have been wearing photo necklaces for about 18 years!!! I get a new one every single year and I store the old ones. It took us awhile, but finally we can add these. This is just the start - we used to have Oliava as my favorite clothing items but that was just too challenging. I talked to my daughters (after the name is created for) and Olivia has been doing jewelry for years. She makes her own bracelets for herself and friends - so we decided we would covert Oliava to photo keepsake items because I was so tired of not finding what I needed! So with the brain of Alex, the creativity of my daughters and my endless ideas...the start of something amazing that will just keep growing.

www.oliava.com

#photonecklaces @photonecklace #anabrandt #oliava #photokeepsake

3-4 months MUST be comfortable on their belly and not teething

6-7 months MUST be comfortable sitting up without being held

11-12 months preferably not walking yet but standing holding onto something or alone.

Our annual Holiday Baby video is here where we feature some of our favorite babies. I photograph hundreds of newborns each year and I wish I could include them all because I love them so much. Here are just a few darling newborns celebrating their first Christmas this year. Thank you to my amazing clients for your trust and patience. I consider this amazing job a privilege and hope I can continue doing it all the days of my life.

Thank you to my children for their support, the staff, the students and of course Alex, who without him this video would not be possible.

May we all live with the wonder and joy that a newborn baby brings.

<3
Merry Christmas 2022
Ana Brandt

Thank you to the amazing models and parents who each drove more than 2 hours for each of the sessions this past weekend in Costa Rica. I so appreciate your time and willingness to be a part of something that I believe is greater than ourselves...the education process. 

Learning is never ending. I feel like I am still learning - about this Industry, the world and most importantly myself.

We are forever evolving and growing because that is what we need to do to not only survive but thrive.

I am now heading home and am excited to see my children and of course be back in my studio. 

It's only day 9 of the year and I have left the country twice already, so hard to believe sometimes that this is my life.
babies + beach the best combination

the best days are here and ahead...

My last trip to Germany is this weekend and then Milan. Next week it’s Thailand/ Philippines and Tokyo.
I don’t have any plans to return to these countries ( except for conferences ) and will most likely be resigning from international travel in two years. 
I have been to 40 Countries and while there are still quite a few on my list to do most of the ones I have been to I won’t be returning. 
This opens the door for future trainers I have a good two years to get them trained and go out in the world. I will be opening up my trainer program one more time before it closes again. Those who signed up for my trainee program you should be in the trainer area in my members app for your training dates- I will be following up with you over the next week along with associates to make sure everyone has training dates.
Traveling internationally has been amazing. It’s given me worldwide recognition and exposed my kids to the huge world we live in. Evan now travels on his own and this year he filmed in Tokyo and and Morocco and I know he has a huge travel schedule ahead of him. My daughters have been around the world and I am sure will journey more as well. I encourage those who do follow my training path to include your family wherever possible. For years I forfeited profits to bring my children with me and it was the best decision I ever made. 
The time is now do not wait for the amazing future that is here. So many times we put off things and if you just give up the fear and amazing world is awaiting you. 
I have one more retreat in Costa Rica and then I will think about future retreats maybe to just once a year.

I received a message yesterday that said "Ana I dont' know what you are doing now but I am in" I feel that all those who signed up for this course said the same thing. All those who signed up for AI said the same thing.I think my kids say the same.I am in - I am in this life...this creative life is what I live and breathe. My kids create non stop. They do audio, video, paint, create endlessly - this is my life and its a creative passionate one and there are no apologies for it. If I die tomorrow, know this - I have lived my life with love, and passion and an urgent need to be the best creative soul I can be. This life is so rich. We have knowledge- we have power to create anything our mind allows. We can love -endlessly - we can forgive - we can create -many of us can give birth - what a gift - with every breathe I breathe I will create and teach my children there are no limits....

see you on the inside
<3

A Morning Message

I went to bed early last night and woke up very early this morning. After a few housekeeping chores I sat down to catch up on client work and thought about what I wanted to say to all of you. Its 8am. Its so quiet in my house. I have 3 kids sleeping and 4 yes 4 dogs. Olivia is home from college and she brought her dog home. My sons girlfriend is also in the home, so there are 8 beating hearts besides my own. I sit in the quiet and think about my life. What did I want growing up? What did I want for my future?. When I was younger I ached to learn about my biological Mom and missing siblings. I yearned to find a place to fit in and many times I just wanted to be alone. I was not very social - I am still not. I wasn’t good in school. I felt out of place and a misfit. As I got older and learned to come into my own and learned to love my Mother - yes as an adopted child I had to learn how to love a new Mother. Something I don’t think people talk about. You don’t just instantly love someone because they take you in - maybe some do, but I didn’t. It took me awhile. Over the years I not only learned to love my new Mother but I needed her with every ounce of my being to guide me into being the woman I am today. She loved me regardless. Regardless of how many times I was in trouble, or didn’t make a good grade. Regardless of all the mistakes I made she always told me she loved me, until the day she passed. She made a decision to love me day one and it was a decision that changed my life, my world and brings me to this keyboard. Being a Mother is everything to me. Its every part of who I am and these three humans mean more to me than anything and anyone in the world. I am not perfect, far from it. My biological Mom and the woman who raised me, my Mother are both now far from this earth and I know at peace. I do thank my biological mother for giving me life at just 18 years of age and not ending it. I will forever be grateful for my Mother for adopting me, raising me and loving me to the ends of her days and raising me to be the woman I am.

At the end of the day we need to love. We just do. Love conquers all. <3 AnaBrandt

Baby Ameline

I shot over 1000 frames in 3.5 hours and directed the other photographers and 3 models though rainstorms, windstorms and bursts of sun. This was the last frame. What you don't see is the rain pouring down soaking us and the models and the immense wind so she could barely stand. At 1/1600 of a second this is the moment captured. I am too tired to look at the rest, need to catch a plane home as I have a beautiful newborn session awaiting in the morning at my studio. I had been battling a migraine for a few days and wasn't feeling my best. That's what you don't see. What do you see? The sheer beauty of this world and the subjects who dwell in it. This is why I love my job and I will do it to the end of my days.

Capturing newborn images within the first few weeks of life is highly recommended for several reasons. .....Firstly, this early stage is a fleeting and unique time in a baby's life. Newborns grow and change so quickly, and their appearance and features can alter noticeably within just a few weeks. By capturing their images during this period, you freeze those precious moments, allowing parents to cherish and remember their baby's tiny, delicate features forever.

Secondly, newborns tend to be more sleepy and flexible during their first few weeks. They are more likely to curl up naturally and comfortably, making it easier to capture those adorable poses and intimate shots that are characteristic of newborn photography. As time goes on, babies become more alert and active, making it challenging to achieve the same level of peacefulness and flexibility.

Additionally, newborns are still adjusting to the world outside the womb during the early weeks of life. They often retain the curly positions and relaxed expressions reminiscent of their time in the womb. These natural poses, combined with their brand-new innocence and vulnerability, create heartwarming and emotive photographs that truly encapsulate the essence of newbornhood.

Lastly, photographing newborns within the first few weeks allows parents to share the joyous news with family and friends promptly. It's a special time when everyone is eagerly awaiting the arrival of the newest family member, and capturing those early images enables parents to introduce their baby to their loved ones, even if they are unable to meet in person..... make sure to get on the schedule as there is limited availability.... www.anabrandt.com...#NewbornPhotography

I started photographing maternity in 1999 - this image is how we all started. Just fabric - black and white - 24 years later the look still looks amazing. Trends come and go but simple classic photography never goes out of style. Next year marks my 25th year in the business. Lots of amazing changes are happening all for the better. I believe at the end of the day to have a long lasting career you have to have a love for your art and your subject - if you have those two things you will never exhaust the endless ideas that will come from doing the work you are called to do.

What if we could not see color of anything - people or food or anything else that we judge based on color.... Then all we could do was judge based on our touch, our sense, our smell, our experiences and all the other senses that are so much more than color. The sound of the voice, the touch of a hand, the smell of the entry of the person that wants to be in our space...what a world that would be.

Today choose YOU

Things I hear all the time…

I am in a small town. {me too}

My town is broke {ummmm not everyone}

Too much competition in my area {competition is fuel}

People only want $200 photographers {not true for everyone}

The economy is terrible - I mean it will always go up and down

No one comments on my posts {ummm me too}

and it goes on and on….

Everything is possible. Is it easy - no! I have been working strong and hard for a long time and I still work very very hard.
People need a reason to come to you. You need to be better than good. You need to be different. Everyone doing the same thing doesn't work. Why are you - well you? 

I would love to see less complaining this season and more hope. 
Shut off social and take an online class. 

Learn AI- put some music on, shut the door and immerse yourself.I beg you, focus on your life, your work, your creations and nevermind anyone else.

Can I say that again.

Nevermind
any
one
else

Someone cheaper than you? 
Not your problem, not your issue.

Someone charging too cheap for a newborn session? 
Not your problem, not your issue.

Someone judging you?
Those are their thoughts not not yours

We can be better and do better.
Let's worry about ourselves. Our behavior.

There are a lot of very very terrible tragedies happening in this world - ask yourself every day how you can make a difference and do it. Whether its in private or public.
I promise you - the less you focus on others and focus inward the more will come out - tenfold.
for the love babies and hope

In the quiet of the night...or day..when you are beyond exhausted...remember this.

This too shall pass. 
There will come a time where you won't be walking around sleep deprived, and you won't hear a baby cry. 

There will come a time when this beautiful new bundle that has exhausted your soul will go out and travel the world. He will roam and meet new people and he will venture far away from home. He won't need you every minute and you won't hear that cry or stare at the monitor. 

But rest assured, he still will need you and he will still love you and you will both forever be a part of who he is. It is everything and so much more. Breathe and tell yourself you got this..you are here for it...every minute...every tear, every cry every ounce of frustration, love, fear and everything in between. 

Because at the end of the day this is what matters...how we love, who we love and how we raise our family. Be kind to yourself today....you are so worth it. 

❤ Ana Brandt

20 years of Santa and I think the Santas Workshop sessions have been my favorite ones. We created a 3D set out of nothing but prompts in AI which generated images that we then could manipulate and edit and enhance. We then had 3 walls printed as a backdrop to create a room. We bought a picnic table that Alex stained on the street in his truck. My daughter Ava found an amazing little Santa radio for our set and Alex found amazing wood crafts. It was a true team effort and so amazing. Watching each child color, paint, and build toys was so amazing. I think having a small building just for this would be amazing. This season requires a little belief to make it magical and that's what kids bring. They bring belief, hope and wonder and without that where would we be. A special thank you to this Santa who saved my soul two years back when I lost two Santas and my Mom to the heavens. He came in and wrapped his big Santa hands around me and has become such a huge part of my studio and my clients history. Thank you Santa - thank you so so much for stepping in and filling this amazing role. We still have one more day left!! 

To my amazing clients who bought this amazing workshop for this year and those who are already signing up for next year, thank you. I love what I do. I love kids. I really do and watching them do this each year...they come in with their wonder, awe and sometimes a little fear...is worth it - it's always worth it.
